SIMPLE: wee
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wee
<hw>Wee</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>we</ets> a bit,
in <ets>a little we</ets>, probably originally meaning, a little way,
the word <ets>we</ets> for <ets>wei</ets> being later taken as
synonymous with <ets>little</ets>. See <er>Way</er>.]</ety> <def>A
little; a bit, as of space, time, or distance.</def> <mark>[Obs. or
Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wee</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Wee
<hw>Wee</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Very small; little.</def>
<mark>[Colloq. & Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A little <qex>wee</qex> face, with a little yellow beard.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Weech-elm</ent>⟦br⟧
